&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SOE is an engineering consulting firm that specializes in electrical, electromechanical, and embedded systems. Founded in 2016, we have 30+ engineers across offices in El Segundo, CA and Redmond, WA. In that time, we’ve completed over 250 projects for more than 100 clients. Our designs control rocket engines, manage satellite communications, instrument fusion reactors, and are enjoyed by consumers around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We approach problems from first principles. We break challenges down to their most fundamental components, which is how we find solutions that hold up across industries, use cases, and engineering functions. We focus on solving the right problems and building the teams to take them on. Because we believe that training and empowering others yields a greater impact than focusing on developing any specific technology, we expect every single member of our team to participate in building up those around them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the past two years, we&#39;ve generated a new avenue of growth. We’ve started taking our own internal concepts and incubating separate companies that we believe will meet the emerging needs of our clients and the industry at large. We currently have two of these companies in stealth that our team is actively working on, one in nuclear energy and one in space telecommunications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Information about SOE’s mission, vision, and values can be found &lt;a href=&quot;https://soeffects.com/about&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Examples of the projects SOE has worked on can be found &lt;a href=&quot;https://soeffects.com/work&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;We are looking for a High Speed Digital Electrical Engineer to work across client programs that demand hardware performing at the edge of what is commercially possible.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;This is a hands-on design role. You will own high-speed digital PCB design, signal integrity, and FPGA development across a range of programs - from space avionics and optical communication systems to power electronics and embedded computing platforms. No two programs are identical, and you will bring the same first-principles rigor to each one.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;You will work alongside engineers who have shipped flight hardware and know what it takes to close a design in a real program environment. You will have direct client exposure, ownership over your technical deliverables, and access to programs that rarely show up at larger firms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;As SOE grows our incubation model, high-speed digital engineering sits at the center of the most technically demanding programs we take on. This role is a direct line into that work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;High Speed Digital Design&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Support high speed electrical architecture from concept generation through investigation including key trades, requirement definition, investigations and component selection.
